Class GraphSimAlgorithm

java.lang.Object
  org.graphstream.stream.SinkAdapter
      gsim.GraphSimAlgorithm
All Implemented Interfaces:
org.graphstream.algorithm.Algorithm, org.graphstream.algorithm.DynamicAlgorithm, org.graphstream.stream.AttributeSink, org.graphstream.stream.ElementSink, org.graphstream.stream.Sink
public class GraphSimAlgorithm
extends org.graphstream.stream.SinkAdapter
implements org.graphstream.algorithm.DynamicAlgorithm

This class is the Simulation algorithm, which is an interface used to communicate between the GraphSim object and the graph stream API to display animations. This handles the simulation job queue. This class should only be called from GraphSim.

Author:
brandon
